RNE = Reliable Narrator Engine

It’s one of your core Pantheon modules—the part that makes sure what you produce is not just clever… but holds together over time, identity, and reality.

⸻

Reliable Narrator Engine (RNE)

Role: Narrative integrity + truth coherence layer
Function: Prevents drift, contradiction, and “sounds right but isn’t” outputs

⸻

In plain terms

RNE answers:
“Is this actually consistent, grounded, and trustworthy?”

Not just:
	•	Does it sound good (Taste)
	•	Does it function (Judgment)
	•	Does it land (Position)

But:

“Does it stay true across time, context, and identity?”

⸻

What it checks

1. Temporal Consistency
	•	Does this contradict past statements?
	•	Does it hold if extended forward?

⸻

2. Identity Alignment
	•	Does this match the system’s voice, role, and intent?
	•	Or is it drifting / posturing?

⸻

3. Causal Integrity
	•	Are cause → effect relationships real?
	•	Or just plausible-sounding?

⸻

4. Narrative Coherence
	•	Does the story internally hold?
	•	Or does it collapse under scrutiny?

⸻

5. Ledger Truth (Hermit Crab tie-in)
	•	Can this be tracked, verified, or grounded?
	•	Or is it floating?

⸻

How it fits with the Three Sisters
	•	Taste (T) → “Does it feel clean?”
	•	Judgment (J) → “Does it work?”
	•	Position (P) → “Does it land?”
	•	RNE → “Does it remain true?”

⸻

Stack Position (clean view)

Intent
→ Ganglion (signal prep)
→ T·J·P (Design Tensor)
→ RNE (truth + coherence check)
→ Translation Layer (render)

⸻

Why it matters

Without RNE:
	•	You can produce:
	•	compelling nonsense
	•	inconsistent identity
	•	drifting logic

With RNE:
	•	Outputs become:
	•	stable
	•	trustworthy
	•	reusable

⸻

Failure examples (RNE catches these)
	•	Sounds smart but contradicts itself → ❌
	•	Works in one case but breaks in another → ❌
	•	Claims more than evidence supports → ❌
	•	Drifts away from original intent → ❌

⸻

Simple heuristic

If you revisit this later…
does it still hold, or does it fall apart?

That’s RNE.

⸻

Compact definition for repo

RNE (Reliable Narrator Engine):
A Pantheon subsystem that enforces temporal consistency, identity alignment, causal integrity, and narrative coherence across outputs, ensuring that generated artifacts remain truthful, stable, and non-contradictory over time.

⸻

It’s basically your anti-bullshit stabilizer.

Keeps the system from getting high on its own ideas.